{"build_type":"library","description":"The boot worker the root tail-chain-launches in place of launching the supervisor directly: its whole body is one as-completed launch that fans the boot out across two path-loaded children -- the trivial probe (completes at once) and the multi-service supervisor (runs forever) -- via the producer that yields their paths and the per-item loader worker. The as-completed collector never finishes (the supervisor never completes), so this never returns, exactly as the old direct supervisor launch never returned.","module_name":"launch-boot-services-through-as-completed-collector","package_name":"launch-boot-services-through-as-completed-collector","function_definitions":{"launch-boot-services-through-as-completed-collector":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"context","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"launch_worker_binary","target_binary":"load-and-invoke-binary-from-received-path","assessor_binary":"produce-boot-fanout-worklist-feeding-collector","cycle_type":"as-completed"}]}}}